heading_context: Check if an alcohol wholesaler is approved
chunks.html_content: If you buy alcohol to sell on, you must check that the wholesaler or producer you buy it from is approved.
chunks.plain_content:
Check if an alcohol wholesaler is approved
If you buy alcohol to sell on, you must check that the wholesaler or producer you buy it from is approved.

heading_context: Check if an alcohol wholesaler is approved
chunks.html_content: You can be fined or go to prison if you buy alcohol from a wholesaler who is not approved.
chunks.plain_content:
Check if an alcohol wholesaler is approved
You can be fined or go to prison if you buy alcohol from a wholesaler who is not approved.

heading_context: Check if an alcohol wholesaler is approved
chunks.html_content:
You do not need to check if you’re an individual buying alcohol for a one-off event, such as a party once a year. You still need to get a licence to sell alcohol, known as a Temporary Events Notice.

You need to check wholesalers from the Isle of Man separately.

heading_context: Check if an alcohol wholesaler is approved
chunks.html_content: You need the wholesaler or producer’s Unique Reference Number (URN). This should be printed on their invoices. Contact them if you cannot find it.
